<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871215-0168 </DOCNO><HL> Biotechnology Firms to Merge</HL><DD> 12/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> DNAP AGSITENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> CINNAMINSON, N.J.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   DNA Plant Technology Corp., an agricultural chemical and biotechnology concern, said it agreed to merge with Oakland, Calif.-based Advanced Genetic Sciences Inc., a developer of disease-resistant plants and other agricultural biotechnologies, in a stock transaction valued at about $36.6 million.    The agreement calls for Advanced Genetic shareholders to receive two-thirds of a share of DNA Plant stock for each share of Advanced Genetic stock. The new company will be named after the merger is completed. </TEXT></DOC>